cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SY, cs.HC, cs.CE 

This paper discusses the management of systems engineering artifacts in the context of agile methods in the automotive industry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also touches upon the communication between stakeholders, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Social Science) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The focus on safety compliance documents and architecture models could also relate to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the mention of a systems engineering tool could suggest cs.CE (Computational Engineering).
